Eight people were killed, and one was injured after a memorial arch collapsed in Taitou village in north China's Hebei Province at 6:28 p.m. Saturday, the local government said in a news release. The 12-meter-tall arch collapsed amid heavy rain and high wind, burying nine residents who were taking shelter. Firefighters were deployed to the scene and later confirmed eight residents were dead. One person was hospitalized and in a stable condition. The Luquan District government, where the accident occurred, is investigating the cause.